00:03:12.350 --> 00:03:15.340
So when I evaluated
this-- right.

00:03:15.340 --> 00:03:17.490
This is right, and then I take
the antiderivative of y to the

00:03:17.490 --> 00:03:21.430
third over 2, I get y
to the fourth over 8.

00:03:21.430 --> 00:03:26.550
And now I evaluate
this at 1 and 0.

00:03:26.550 --> 00:03:27.540
And that give us what?

00:03:27.540 --> 00:03:34.290
1/6 minus 1/8 minus-- well both
of these when you evaluate

00:03:34.290 --> 00:03:35.410
them, are going to be 0's.

00:03:35.410 --> 00:03:37.700
So this is going to be
another 0 minus 0.

00:03:37.700 --> 00:03:38.530
So you don't have to
worry about that.

00:03:38.530 --> 00:03:41.000
So what's 1/6 minus 1/8?

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:41.930
Let's see.

00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:43.310
24.

00:03:43.310 --> 00:03:50.070
That's 4 minus 3 over 24, which
is equal to 1/24-- is the

00:03:50.070 --> 00:03:51.600
volume of our figure.

00:03:55.640 --> 00:04:00.280
So this time, the way we just
