00:06:28.600 --> 00:06:28.970
Right?

00:06:28.970 --> 00:06:32.000
So the curve is the upper
bound when we go upwards.

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:34.130
And what is the upper
bound on the curve?

00:06:34.130 --> 00:06:37.680
Well we're holding x
fixed, so for any given

00:06:37.680 --> 00:06:40.300
x what is this point?

00:06:40.300 --> 00:06:41.730
Well that's going
to be x squared.

00:06:41.730 --> 00:06:42.000
Right?

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:43.940
Because this is the graph
of y equals x squared.

00:06:43.940 --> 00:06:48.700
So our upper bound is y
is equal to x squared.

00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:49.800
And what's our lower bound?

00:06:49.800 --> 00:06:52.310
We can keep adding these
squares down here.

00:06:52.310 --> 00:06:54.550
We're adding all the
little changes in y.

00:06:54.550 --> 00:06:55.610
So what's our lower bound?

